{
  "stem": "11723.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my-- my uncle whose wife went insane, invited us down to-- again to Kiskoros because his wife's family owned vineyards there.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was plenty food there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And besides, he had two children and his wife couldn't take care of them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "His wife needed taking care of, so he said to my mother, you come down, take care of the kids and my wife, and you'll have plenty of food and everything.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And by the way, something that I left out earlier, the entire Katz family had put everything together in a safe-- dollars, gold, diamonds, all kinds of valuables, jewelry.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And before the war, a member of the family took it down to Kiskoros to these people who were called Schwartz, who had the vineyards.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were supposed to bury it underground someplace and keep it for everybody for after the war.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because otherwise, the Germans took everything away or the Hungarians, one or the other-- mostly the Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Before the Germans got to us, the Hungarians did a good job.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Anyway, so everything from the Katz family went down there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Everything from the Schwartz family, everything from the Gluck family.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Whatever everybody had, almost everything went there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Except for the money that was in numbered Swiss accounts from my grandmother, but no one knows where it is because my grandmother died.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the money she sent out to this country, to California, which we got when we got to this country.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But the stuff that was sent down-- the valuables that were sent down to Kiskoros, we never found.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "First of all, the Schwartz family-- the entire Schwartz family was taken to Auschwitz, and not one person survived.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So there was no one who knew where it was buried.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
